            <title>[HBASE-4500] [replication] Add a delayed option</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4500</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A typical DR solution with databases is to have one slave that receives data a few hours late to guard against destructive operations. On top of my head one way to implement this would be tail the log, see how current the edit is, sleep if needed, replicate, repeat.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The harder part will be adding a configuration to the stream.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
